  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Battling Misinformation and Promoting Rights and Freedoms in Jordan Through Media Literacy</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project came in response to the recent COVID-19 pandemic which highlighted the urgent need for iindividuals  to have access to verifaction and fact-checking skills as well as the importance of access to information and  freedoms of press and expression. It is within the action plan of the National Media and Information Literacy (MIL) Initiative was adopted by the Jordanian government in 2019. Jordan Media Institue is the implementing arm of the initiative which includes a component to engage Civil Society Organizations. It will be implemented in coordination with the Minister of Culture whose office is handling the portfolio on behalf of the government.</narrative>
  </description>
